transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, thank you so much for calling Bazaar Day.

Speaker 2: My name is Jessie.

Speaker 1: Can I get your first and last name?

Speaker 2: Hi, Jessie.

Speaker 1: Felix Perez.

Speaker 2: Great.

Speaker 1: Mr. Perez, what can I help you with?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I made a purchase before.

Speaker 1: It was just one bottle.

Speaker 2: I'm thinking of making another purchase,

Speaker 1: but I'm reluctant to do it because I'm going on a trip next week,

Speaker 2: and I'm afraid that I am not going to get that delivery before then.

Speaker 1: In time?

Speaker 2: Yeah, it's highly likely that may happen because it's this time of year.

Speaker 1: Mail is just the worst.

Speaker 2: It might be better to wait.

Speaker 1: I mean, like how long will you be out for?

Speaker 2: And when exactly are you leaving next week?

Speaker 1: I believe Wednesday evening.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I don't think it will make it, honestly.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: How long, in your estimation, do you think, more or less, do you think?

Speaker 1: Where are you located?

Speaker 2: Hold on one second.

Speaker 1: Let me see here.

Speaker 2: Felix Perez, right?

Speaker 1: Yep.

Speaker 2: Ooh, you're in the Bronx?

Speaker 1: You're all the way – yeah, it's shipping out of California.

Speaker 2: That's easily going to take you seven to ten days.

Speaker 1: Yeah, okay.

Speaker 2: All right, I should have made that purchase before.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: All right, thank you, Jessie.

Speaker 1: You're welcome.

Speaker 2: Have a good day.

Speaker 1: Bye.
